rubbers-pipsOut.name: Air UPUPUPUP with sponge
rubbers-pipsOut.desc: Probably this is going to be cannon (white air sponge around 38deg), but may be substituted with other sponges of similar cost, or I may match sponges with the selection. Whatever I use it will be at least the quality of the factory sponge that normally comes under the pips, and probably much better. Be aware that many of the long pips with thin base are difficult for me to glue perfectly, but I think on average I do as good of a job as can be done.

rubbers-sponges.name: Air Supersoft 30
rubbers-sponges.desc: Generally speaking the lemon sponges are the variety that have the most bubbles, and thus are the lightest. They are generally easier to sink the ball into. In thinner versions, the ball will go to the blade easily compared to other, denser makes.
